From: Martin Schiller <ms@dev.tdt.de>
Date: Tue, 2 Dec 2025 10:27:16 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Revert "clk: mxl: Add option to override gate clks"

Revert commit a5d49bd369b8 ("clk: mxl: Add option to override gate
clks").

There was added a flag to select if a clock gate should be controlled by
the CGU clk driver or directly by the PMU / EPU and the default behavior
was changed to "controlled by EPU". But this defacto broke / disabled
the clock gate handling. As long as there is no driver for the EPU, this
flag is useless and we want to control the clock gates by the clk
driver.

Fixes: a5d49bd369b8 ("clk: mxl: Add option to override gate clks")
Signed-off-by: Martin Schiller <ms@dev.tdt.de>
---
 drivers/clk/x86/clk-cgu.c | 16 +---------------
 drivers/clk/x86/clk-cgu.h |  3 +--
 2 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 17 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/clk/x86/clk-cgu.c b/drivers/clk/x86/clk-cgu.c
index 89b53f280aee..123c6dcea5de 100644
--- a/drivers/clk/x86/clk-cgu.c
+++ b/drivers/clk/x86/clk-cgu.c
@@ -355,22 +355,8 @@ int lgm_clk_register_branches(struct lgm_clk_provider *ctx,
 			hw = lgm_clk_register_fixed_factor(ctx, list);
 			break;
 		case CLK_TYPE_GATE:
-			if (list->gate_flags & GATE_CLK_HW) {
-				hw = lgm_clk_register_gate(ctx, list);
-			} else {
-				/*
-				 * GATE_CLKs can be controlled either from
-				 * CGU clk driver i.e. this driver or directly
-				 * from power management driver/daemon. It is
-				 * dependent on the power policy/profile requirements
-				 * of the end product. To override control of gate
-				 * clks from this driver, provide NULL for this index
-				 * of gate clk provider.
-				 */
-				hw = NULL;
-			}
+			hw = lgm_clk_register_gate(ctx, list);
 			break;
-
 		default:
 			dev_err(ctx->dev, "invalid clk type\n");
 			return -EINVAL;
diff --git a/drivers/clk/x86/clk-cgu.h b/drivers/clk/x86/clk-cgu.h
index bcaf8aec94e5..6d63e2916260 100644
--- a/drivers/clk/x86/clk-cgu.h
+++ b/drivers/clk/x86/clk-cgu.h
@@ -197,8 +197,7 @@ struct lgm_clk_branch {
 /* clock flags definition */
 #define CLOCK_FLAG_VAL_INIT	BIT(16)
 #define MUX_CLK_SW		BIT(17)
-#define GATE_CLK_HW		BIT(18)
-#define DIV_CLK_NO_MASK		BIT(19)
+#define DIV_CLK_NO_MASK		BIT(18)
 
 #define LGM_MUX(_id, _name, _pdata, _f, _reg,		\
 		_shift, _width, _cf, _v)		\
